  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Grant Aid in Response to the Humanitarian Crisis in Burkina Faso, Chad and Niger</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The upsurge of violence in Burkina Faso in the form of armed attacks and insecurity in the Sahel, Centre Nord, Nord, Boucle du Mouhoun and Est regions has triggered an unprecedented humanitarian emergency marked by mass displacements and disruption of access to basic social services. Through this project, IOM&apos;s response seeks to improve humanitarian assistance to internally displaced persons and host communities in Burkina Faso by enabling those crisis-affected population to cope with the shocks of displacement and reduce risk of secondary displacement through livelihood opportunities, shelter assistance, and protection activities.</narrative>
  </description>
